oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Cow Calf Practice in the Midwest
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Iliff, Ruel "Buzz"
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: I would like to present a case from a few years ago. I have been working with this herd since 1994. It started with 50 cows and is currently at 200 cows arid calve out 40 heifers annually. It is a commercial herd, Angus base and crossed with Gelbvieh to produce Fl females. The herd is well managed, nutrition is top notch and the herd is tracked on cow sense records.
